Police have shot and killed a suspect wanted for a string of crimes in Johannesburg. Courtesy of #DSTV403 KATLEHONG - Police have shot and killed a man wanted for a string of crimes in Johannesburg. The man had been on the run and began firing at the police when found in Katlehong on Saturday. READ: JMPD to escort medics to crime hotspots A shoot-out ensued and officers fatally wounded him. SAPS spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo said the 41-year-old man was wanted for murder, attempted murder, arson, and assault. Masondo stated that no police officers were harmed in the exchange of fire.